Pregnancy Overview

Pregnancy lasts about 40 weeks, counted from the first day of the last period, even though conception happens around week 2.

First Trimester (Weeks 1-12)

  • Common Symptoms: Missed periods, nausea, tiredness, frequent urination
  • Development: Baby's heart starts beating, major organs form
  • Miscarriage Risk: About 1 in 4 pregnancies

Second Trimester (Weeks 13-27)

  • More energy, growing belly, baby movements felt
  • Baby can move, cry silently, and suck thumb
  • Gestational diabetes test around weeks 24-28

Third Trimester (Weeks 28-40)

  • Fatigue, back pain, breathlessness
  • Baby moves into birth position by week 36
  • Full term at week 40
